Exploring Virtual Reality (VR) Technology
---------------------------------------
Virtual Reality (VR) is an immersive technology that creates a simulated environment, allowing users to experience a sense of presence in a virtual world. Using headsets, sensors, and controllers, VR enables users to interact with 3D worlds in real-time, making it widely popular in gaming, education, and training. VR is transforming fields like healthcare, where it aids in surgical simulations, and education, where it offers interactive learning experiences. As VR technology advances, it opens doors to more engaging, realistic, and personalized applications across various industries.

